<br>
<br>
Jagged Blade of War<br>
Warrior Epic Quest<br>
Updated by:<br>
Millain Velves D’Phalar<br>
 <br>
Kargak Redblade is standing next to a Dwarf named Wenden in East Freeport. To get to them, head in the gate from North Ro and follow the left wall. They both start the quest. <br>
<br>
Hilt # 1 - Jeweled Dragon Head Hilt <br>
<br>
Head to Lake Rathe to get the unjeweled dragon head hilt. You can find it spawning on the lake floor underneath the 3 aviak spawn tower. Now, you need to get a Diamond, Black Sapphire, and a Jacinth. You'll find them in the planes, high lvl dungeons such as sebilis, or from the dino in the ocean of tears. <br>
<br>
Take the Unjeweled dragon head hilt Diamond, Jacinth, and black Saphire to the dwarf Wenden. Hand him all 4 items you will recieve the Jeweled Dragon Head Hilt. <br>
<br>
Hilt #2 - Finely Crafted Dragon Head Hilt <br>
<br>
Head to Timorous Deep. It is best to have a druid cast levitate and sow on you to do this. Run down to the southwest corner of the zone, where you'll find the chessboard (loc –6500, +3000). You do not have to have Levitate and SoW, if you get on the Bloated Belly and head towards The Overthere, the Island will be on your right if you are facing the front of the boat.  It will be shortly after you pass the sunken ships to your left.  At the base of the king peice, there is a small bag dropped on the ground - pick it up and you get the Damaged Dragon Head Hilt. <br>
<br>
Next, head to the Plane of Fear. The item you are looking for is a Ball of Everliving Golem. This drops from the named golems Fright, level 50 and 14,325 HP’s, Dread, level 51 and 15,615 HP’s, and Terror, Level 52 and 16,970 HP’s.  These are the personal guardians to Cazic Thule and they spawn at the temple.  It may also drop off of cazic and the dracoliche. <br>
<br>
Now go to the Dreadlands, to the Giant castle just west of Karnor castle zone. Kill every giant you see, in hopes of getting the Mountin Giant Patriarch, a Level 47 Mountain Giant, to spawn. One of his rarer drops is the Giant Monocle (this is not no drop, so you can also trade for it). Take the Monocle to Frontier Mountians. Get to the giant fort and get inside. When you get to the very end of the Mine you will see the giant named Mentrax Mountainbone. Hand him the Monocle he will give you Rejesium Ore. Now run back to Freeport east with the ore and the ball. Hand the ore, ball and Damaged Dragon Head Hilt to Wenden and he will give you the Finely Crafted Dragon Head Hilt. <br>
<br>
Sword Blade # 1 - Ancient Sword Blade <br>
<br>
Talk to Denken Strongpick, on aviak island in the Ocean of Tears. He'll tell you what he wants for this rusty old blade he found on the ocean floor: <br>
<br>
a) A keg of vox tail ale - bought from alot of vendors around the world (100-200pp depending upon your Charisma). A good place to buy one is the sandfishers in north ro or the freeport port authority <br>
<br>
b) A Block Of Perma frost - Dropped by Ice giants.  You MUST kill the Ice Giants inside Permafrost, and they are estimated 48-52 level.  They hit hard and fast, over 100 damage most of the time, and they have tons of hitpoints! While you're here, kill some goblin wizards and pick up the frozen goblin heart ... you'll need it later.  The Block of Permafrost IS NOT no drop, so it can also be bought or traded for. <br>
<br>
c) Rebreathers - Tinkered by gnomes. Expect to drop as much as 4k for getting two rebreathers.  I got lucky and was able to buy mine for 1500pp each.  Rebreathers become Trivial at 175. <br>
<br>
Turn the 2 rebreathers, the keg of vox tail ale, and the block of permafrost in to the dwarf and you will get the 1st blade. <br>
<br>
Sword Blade # 2 - Ancient Blade <br>
<br>
This is dropped by the Queen of Chardok, Queen Velazul. Bring along a large group, as she is level 62 with 22,020 Hitpoints.  She is a shaman with many AE spells such as High Damage and Poison.  She can be mesmerized, and has been stated that you need to keep her stunned, and you should buff versus FIRE. You will probably have to kill here several times before she coughs this up.  It has been said Verant has upped the drop rate on this blade… <br>
<br>
The Red Scabbard <br>
<br>
Talk to Kargak Redblade in east freeport - next to Wenden and say [I will do you a favor]. You get a letter ( wax sealed note). Take this letter to an Ogre in Ferrott named Oknoggin. He hangs out between the Stone bridge and the Fallen totem. Hand him the letter and he gives you a Tiny Lute. <br>
<br>
Run back to East Freeport And give the Tiny Lute to Kargek Redblade he gives you a book. Now take the book over to his brother in East Karana - Tenal Redblade, who is at the very end of the canyon next to the ramp to Highpass. Hand him the book,and he gives you a Frozen War Totem. <br>
<br>
Hand him back the totem and the Frozen Goblin Heart that you got from perma (YOU DID remeber to get one while you camped the Ice Giants right?) and he gives you back the Totem of Fiery war. <br>
<br>
You then need to return the totem to Tenal Redblade, along with a Green Dragon Scale and a Red Dragon scale, and he gives you The Mark of the Sword. <br>
<br>
<br>
Red Dragon Scale drops off of Lord Nagafen, a level 55 dragon with 32,000 hitpoints, in Nagafens Lair, he CANNOT be mesmerized and he has the ability to summon you.  Talendor, a level 60 dragon with 32,000 Hitpoints.  Talendor can hit for 520 damage, he CAN be Mesmerized.  It can also be found off Zordakilicus Ragefire, a 54 Level dragon. He spawns after killing the NPS vendor that spawns after killing Lord Nagafen.  The NPC Vendor can spawn anywhere from right after Lord Nagafen dies, to 80 hours after he dies.  There is now a fourth way to get a Red Dragon scale.  In The Hole, there is a MOB called, Nortlav Scalekeeper, he is Level 55.  He hits for 190 average, and has a nasty harmtouch that does around 1500 damage, and has HIGH Magic Resist.  Wizard spells, Lure Line and Ice Comet will stick.  Necromancer DoT’s also work well.<br>
 Green Dragon Scale drops off of Severilous, a level 60 dragon with 32,000 Hitpoints, who lives in Emerald Jungle.  He CAN be mesmerized, and he hits for 520 damage.  The Green Scales now drop off an additional MOB, which was added on 6.27.2001, Hoshkar in Veeshan’s Peak.  He is a Level 65 dragon and can only be killed by very UBER Guilds, or very large groups.  <br>
<br>
<br>
 Now head to the Plane of Hate and kill  the level 53 follower of Innoruuk, Maestro of Rancor, He can be found sitting at his piano.  Be careful, he has a 200 Hitpoint AoE lifetap spell.  Once he has been killed, a small hand which looks like a fright finger, spawns at the piano.  When killing it, make sure you keep it rooted as it runs really fast when it gets low on health.  After you kill this hand, another hand will spawn which is called, The Hand of Maestro.  This hits hard and has a ton of hitpoints. You need to get his hand, which is a rare drop. Bring that back and give it to Tenal aong with the mark and he gives you a note to Kargek and yet another, final quest. <br>
<br>
You need a Spiroc Wingblade from the Spiroc Lord in the Plane of Sky, he is level 63 and also has a pet which is no higher than level 25.  This is one of the hardest creatures to beat in the Plane of Sky. You then take the Winglbade and the note to Kargek where he gives you the Red Scabbard and instructions to combine the Ancient Blade, Ancient Sword Blade, Finely Crafted Dragon Head Hilt, and Jeweled Dragon Head Hilt to receive your reward. <br>
<br>
The Two Handed Sword splits into the two One Handed Swords, which can then be recombined into the 2HS.<br>
<br>
