<br>
Being KOS in Freeport will be a bit of a problem, since you have to go there several times.  Might I suggest killing all the orcs you can find in EC and buying all the Df Belts you can get your hands on 1-2pp, depends how desperate you are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Once you are to dubious (by killing tons and tons of orcs) You will be able to start turning in DF belts, and that makes it a lot faster to become indiff.  I did this long enough, that on my last run I had just bought 18 belts, turned them in figured cool I'll be indiff, I was amiable to guards.  By the way, I know Tarsk already knows me, but I am a Dark Elf <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It can be done.<br>
